author: Russell Brand
description:
Is this really about defending America—or defending someone else’s war?

Iran and Israel are at war, and America’s already getting dragged in. In this episode, I unpack how we got here, what Tucker Carlson and Trump are saying, and why this could be the defining moment of U.S. foreign policy. Is it really “America First” if we’re always the ones picking up the tab for someone else’s war? And what does it mean spiritually to stay neutral—or to pick a side?

author: Russell Brand
description:
Today I’m joined by Dave Rubin to talk about civil unrest, common sense governance, and what happens when the media deliberately misrepresents reality. We get into the protests, the problem with blocking roads, and what it really means to live in a free society. Dave shares stories about local policing in Florida, how DeSantis is handling the chaos, and why Trump’s vilification might have opened the door to something even darker.
